		<exercises>
		<title>Activities: Summarize What You Learned</title>
		<exercise xml:id="x_summarize-energy">
		<title>Conservation</title>
    <p>
      In studying energy and momentum, you learned about conservation laws, which provide a different perspective on the world than forces do.  Summarize the conservation laws you learned about, including information about <em>when</em> each quantity is conserved. 
    </p>
		</exercise>
		<exercise>
		<title>Analysis</title>
    <p>
      You have now learned several different ways to analyze a context: forces, energy, and momentum.  All three of them are valid, but they are not all equally useful in different situations.  Write a few sentences summarizing when and how you want to use each strategy going forward.
    </p>
		</exercise>
